Package: quics
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, openssl
Description: QUIC File Transfer and Remote Command Execution
 QUICS is a secure file transfer and remote command execution application
 built on the QUIC protocol using quic-go. It provides mutual TLS
 authentication, configurable command whitelisting, and support for running
 commands as specific users/groups on Linux systems.
 .
 Features:
  * Secure mutual authentication with X.509 certificates
  * File upload/download with binary and ASCII modes
  * Remote command execution with configurable whitelist
  * Interactive client mode with local command execution
  * Configurable connection timeouts and keepalive
  * Linux-specific user/group impersonation for commands